docs.lead_paragraph: FRIEND FITCH: I avail myself of the opportunity of a day's rest to address you note No. 3. Since I last wrote you from Council Grove, we have been steadily pursuing our onward march, and getting along finely; the command enjoying excellent health.

docs.lead_paragraph: THE FAMOUS MRS. WILSON.--Mrs. WILSON whose captivity among the Comanches, and heart-rending sufferings and misfortunes, some time last year created a universal interest and sympathy throughout the country, came up in the stage on Tuesday night last, and will leave in a few days for one of the Eastern counties where some of her friends reside.

docs.lead_paragraph: Cholera. There were two deaths from Cholera on Staten Island yesterday morning; one, Mrs. BURTON, a young married lady living at Tompkinsville--the other, a child in the same neighborhood. Neither had been ill a day. It was reported the husband of the lady was also lying ill with the discase.
